problem_prompt: You are an expert in number theory. Solve the following problem. What is the greatest common divisor of $7979$ and $3713$?
solution:
We can use the Euclidean Algorithm to find the greatest common divisor of these two integers. \begin{align*}
\gcd(7979, 3713) &= \gcd(3713, 7979 - 2\cdot 3713) \\
&= \gcd(3713, 553) \\
&= \gcd(553, 3713 - 6\cdot 553) \\
&= \gcd(553, 395) \\
&= \gcd(395, 553 - 395) \\
&= \gcd(395, 158) \\
&= \gcd(158, 395- 2\cdot 158) \\
&= \gcd(158, 79) \\
&= \boxed{79}.
\end{align*}
gpt_response:
To find the greatest common divisor of $7979$ and $3713$, we can use the Euclidean algorithm:

$7979 = 2(3713) + 1553$
$3713 = 2(1553) + 607$
$1553 = 2(607) + 339$
$607 = 1(339) + 268$
$339 = 1(268) + 71$
$268 = 3(71) + 55$
$71 = 1(55) + 16$
$55 = 3(16) + 7$
$16 = 2(7) + 2$
$7 = 3(2) + 1$

Since the last non-zero remainder in the above calculation is 1, the greatest common divisor of $7979$ and $3713$ is 1.
